    "spell": {
        "name": "Swear Oath",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "You loudly and firmly state a course of action that you swear to fulfill. When you Cast this Spell, Ready a single action or free action you can use. If the action is in line with your personal edicts or the edicts presented by your religion, you can Cast this Spell as a single action. If the trigger you designate occurs and you can use the chosen action as a reaction, you gain a +1 status bonus to any attack roll or skill check required. If the trigger you designate doesn\u2019t occur, you can Sustain the spell on your next turn to regain the Focus Point spent for this spell.",
        "subtype": "spell",
        "spell_type": "focus",
